# No Harness file-permission prompts

- Harness must remain usable when protected folders are unavailable.
- Never open `NSOpenPanel` automatically in response to a background read, launch refresh, or permission error.
- A denied file read becomes unavailable data and a plain in-app status; it never becomes an approval task for Adam.
- Never launch the macOS Harness app with `CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`. The project-local runner must preserve the stable Apple Development identity from `project.yml`.
- Verify every Harness build with `codesign` and inspect the live app for permission dialogs before claiming this bug is fixed.
